defs.name: powi
defs.docs: Raise a number to an integer power.

defs.name: powf
defs.docs: Raise a number to a real number power.

defs.name: sqrt
defs.docs: Take the square root of a number.

defs.name: exp
defs.docs: Returns `e^(self)`, (the exponential function).

defs.name: exp2
defs.docs: Returns `2^(self)`.

defs.name: ln
defs.docs: Returns the natural logarithm of the number.

defs.name: log
defs.docs: Returns the logarithm of the number with respect to an arbitrary base.

defs.name: log2
defs.docs: Returns the base 2 logarithm of the number.

defs.name: log10
defs.docs: Returns the base 10 logarithm of the number.

defs.name: to_degrees
defs.docs: Converts radians to degrees.

defs.name: to_radians
defs.docs: Converts degrees to radians.

defs.name: max
defs.docs: Returns the maximum of the two numbers.

defs.name: min
defs.docs: Returns the minimum of the two numbers.

defs.name: abs_sub
defs.docs: The positive difference of two numbers.

defs.name: cbrt
defs.docs: Take the cubic root of a number.

defs.name: hypot
defs.docs:
Calculate the length of the hypotenuse of a right-angle triangle given
 legs of length `x` and `y`.

defs.name: sin
defs.docs: Computes the sine of a number (in radians).

defs.name: cos
defs.docs: Computes the cosine of a number (in radians).

defs.name: tan
defs.docs: Computes the tangent of a number (in radians).

defs.name: asin
defs.docs:
Computes the arcsine of a number. Return value is in radians in
 the range [-pi/2, pi/2] or NaN if the number is outside the range
 [-1, 1].

defs.name: acos
defs.docs:
Computes the arccosine of a number. Return value is in radians in
 the range [0, pi] or NaN if the number is outside the range
 [-1, 1].

defs.name: atan
defs.docs:
Computes the arctangent of a number. Return value is in radians in the
 range [-pi/2, pi/2];

defs.name: atan2
defs.docs: Computes the four quadrant arctangent of `self` (`y`) and `other` (`x`).

defs.name: sin_cos
defs.docs:
Simultaneously computes the sine and cosine of the number, `x`. Returns
 `(sin(x), cos(x))`.

defs.name: exp_m1
defs.docs:
Returns `e^(self) - 1` in a way that is accurate even if the
 number is close to zero.

defs.name: ln_1p
defs.docs:
Returns `ln(1+n)` (natural logarithm) more accurately than if
 the operations were performed separately.

defs.name: sinh
defs.docs: Hyperbolic sine function.

defs.name: cosh
defs.docs: Hyperbolic cosine function.

defs.name: tanh
defs.docs: Hyperbolic tangent function.

defs.name: asinh
defs.docs: Inverse hyperbolic sine function.

defs.name: acosh
defs.docs: Inverse hyperbolic cosine function.

defs.name: atanh
defs.docs: Inverse hyperbolic tangent function.

defs.name: is_negative
defs.docs: Returns true if the number is negative and false if the number is zero or positive.

defs.name: Num
defs.docs:
The base trait for numeric types, covering `0` and `1` values,
 comparisons, basic numeric operations, and string conversion.

defs.name: from_str_radix
defs.docs: Convert from a string and radix <= 36.

defs.name: NumOps
defs.value:
NumOps<Rhs = Self, Output = Self>: Add<Rhs, Output = Output> + Sub<Rhs, Output = Output> + Mul<Rhs, Output =
Output> + Div<Rhs, Output = Output> + Rem<Rhs, Output = Output>
defs.docs: The trait for types implementing basic numeric operations

defs.name: NumRef
defs.docs:
The trait for `Num` types which also implement numeric operations taking
 the second operand by reference.

defs.name: RefNum
defs.value: RefNum<Base>: NumOps<Base, Base> + for<'r> NumOps<&'r Base, Base>
defs.docs:
The trait for references which implement numeric operations, taking the
 second operand either by value or by reference.

defs.name: NumAssignOps
defs.value:
NumAssignOps<Rhs = Self>: AddAssign<Rhs> + SubAssign<Rhs> + MulAssign<Rhs> + DivAssign<Rhs> +
RemAssign<Rhs>
defs.docs: The trait for types implementing numeric assignment operators (like `+=`).

defs.name: NumAssign
defs.docs: The trait for `Num` types which also implement assignment operators.

defs.name: NumAssignRef
defs.docs:
The trait for `NumAssign` types which also implement assignment operations
 taking the second operand by reference.

defs.value: fn <T> (input: T, min: T, max: T) -> T
defs.docs: A value bounded by a minimum and a maximum
